UML:TaggedValue.value: A StoryNode is an ActivityNode that contains a single StoryPattern, which represents a graph transformation. This graph transformation is performed when the StoryNode is executed. If the tranformation is successful/fails, the StoryNode can be left with a SUCCESS/FAILURE edge.

UML:TaggedValue.value: An ActivityEdge can be guarded via NONE, meaning the edge is always taken, SUCCESS/FAILURE meaning the edge is only taken if execution of the ActivityNode was successful/failed. For a StoryNode that is a forEach node, there must be an outgoing edge guarded with EACH_TIME, which is repeated for all matches, and an outgoing edge with an END guard, which is taken when all matches have been treated.

The specification of the control flow of an SDM (== implementation of a method), can be viewed as a graph consisting of nodes and edges. In the metamodel the entire graph is referred to as an Activity, nodes are called ActivityNodes and edges ActivityEdges. The Activity knows the eOperation it implements.
